Former Super Eagles midfielder and coach, Sunday Oliseh, has reacted to the performance of Wilfred Ndidi in Leicester City’s 2-0 Win over Arsenal on Saturday. Ndidi delivered a classy, composed display yet again at the King Power Stadium. Oliseh applauded the midfield enforcer for representing Nigeria well. The former Juventus star tweeted, “What a player! Congrats Wilfred Ndidi, really keeping the Naija flag flying high.” The 22-year-old has been a key member of Brendan Rodgers side who are challenging at the top of the Premier League table. Ndidi notched in a 100% final third pass accuracy, 90% pass accuracy, most tackles won on the pitch and 5 ball recoveries in the game on Saturday night. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.